µC0Ghandy:µC3 How well do companies pay attention to your work-life balance?

µC0J.O.E.:µC4 In a job like this one has to take care of oneself. Productions are usually quite conscious about health and safety and tolerant to people's circumstances. However, the overall life balance and health is in my own hands. I make sure that I get daily exercise and that I don't eat things that are somewhat healthy. This is much easier when working from home than being somewhere in another country. 

During my last production they moved my office next to the office kitchen filled with terrible snacks – I did not fare too well. Working the weight off right now.

µF0µC1How will you spend your years in retirement?µC0µF1

µC0Ghandy:µC3 And what will you do when you reach retirement age? Can you keep your feet still and enjoy a drink by the sea? Will you prefer to play with the grandchildren? Or will you come to a demo party with your walker or crutches?

µC0J.O.E.:µC4 I want to work in this job until I have enough of it and who knows when that will be. Just got to stay fit and healthy.

Once the time has come to retire, I'm looking forward to do all the things mentioned above and more. I have a lot of vintage Amigas and other hardware that would need my attention and I can imagine that I would break out the paint and brushes on a regular basis.

µC0Ghandy:µC3 Or to put it in a nutshell: How should we imagine Peter Baustaedter as a pensioner?

µC0J.O.E.:µC4 Easy – just as obnoxious as I am right now ;)

